					li(itemprop="ingredients") 1 large spoonful of peanut butter (optional)
					li(itemprop="ingredients") A drizzle of high oleic sunflower oil, avocado oil, or extra virgin olive oil		

			div.recipe-directions
				ol(itemprop="recipeInstructions")
					li Combine batter, milk, egg, and peanut butter in a large bowl, mixing until clumps are gone. Use more pancake mix for added thickness and protein content.

					li Heat a large frying pan over medium heat with a small drizzle of oil to coat the surface. Pour batter to make 2-3 pancakes at around a 4-inch diameter

					li Immediately distribute berries and banana slices into the batter. Press the fruit down a little if your batter is thick.

					li Keep at medium heat, and flip once the bottom edges have a golden brown color, or when the batter begins to thicken visibly from the top. 

					li After flipping, the fruit may caramelize and stick to the pan a little. Carefully remove after they've browned and transfer to a plate!
